content.description: Start on the north side of the boulder in a short horizontal crack about 3 feet off the deck. Move into the main horizontal crack a foot higher and traverse right until you get to the south side of the boulder. Get established in the vertical crack and jam/ring lock your way to the top. Easiest way down was to stem against the neighboring boulder.
content.location: From Cat Scratch, walk north towards the power lines about 50 yards.

content.description: Some weird, uneven features inside the crack rewards creative jams.
content.location: From the rock pile head WNW parallel to the road about 100 yards. The crack faces the road.

content.description: Pretty right leaning finger tips crack. My meat hooks couldn’t really fit in which added some difficulty but the very top is perfect fingers.
content.location: From the Pull Out Pile, walk 3 min north to the road, go east to the gate and it should be north about 50 yards from there.

content.description: There is a large pile of boulders with some awkward landings and high ball potential problems. There are several smaller scattered boulders within 5 min walking distance of this pile as well.
